SLS 26RS-393 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 23
BY SENATOR CATHEY
AGRICULTURAL COMMODITIES. Creates the Agricultural-Based National Security
Priorities Task Force.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To create and provide for the Agricultural-Based National Security Priorities Task Force.
3 WHEREAS, Louisiana's diverse agriculture industry, encompassing crops, timber,
4 livestock, and fisheries, is a major contributor to the state's economy; and
5 WHEREAS, agricultural production, food processing, manufacturing, and farm labor
6 systems together form a critical supply chain necessary to sustain food production; and
7 WHEREAS, global disruptions, geopolitical competition, and technological
8 vulnerabilities have exposed weaknesses in agricultural supply chains that could threaten
9 food production and farm operations; and
10 WHEREAS, protecting agricultural land, supporting farmers, and ensuring the
11 stability of food production starts by strengthening domestic agricultural supply chains and
12 farm security; and
13 WHEREAS, Louisiana should take a proactive role in identifying and addressing
14 vulnerabilities affecting agricultural supply chains in order to maintain reliable food
15 production and protecting rural economies.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
17 establish and provide for the Agricultural-Based National Security Priorities Task Force to
18 study farm security, domestic supply chain resilience, and ways to support farmers and food
