1 production in the state, and to propose recommendations, together with specific proposals
2 for legislation, by written report to the legislature and to the David R. Poynter Legislative
3 Research Library as required by R.S. 24:771 and 772, no later than March 21, 2027.
4 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force should consider and make policy
5 recommendations on the following:
6 (1) Enforcement of state laws limiting purchase of agricultural land by
7 Chinese-owned entities.
8 (2) Vulnerabilities related to the use of Chinese-made drones and artificial
9 intelligence technology.
10 (3) Recommendations to secure legal immigration-based farm labor.
11 (4) Incentives for state-based investments in new fertilizer production and
12 other incentives needed to strengthen domestic supply chain for agricultural inputs.
13 (5) Identifying vulnerabilities in food production.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
15 members:
16 (1) The chairman of the Senate Committee on Agriculture, Forestry,
17 Aquaculture, and Rural Development, or his designee.
18 (2) The chairman of the House Committee on Agriculture, Forestry,
19 Aquaculture, and Rural Development, or his designee.
20 (3) A representative appointed by the president of the Senate, representing
21 the aquaculture industry.
22 (4) A representative appointed by the speaker of the House of
23 Representatives, representing the cattle industry.
24 (5) The commissioner of the Louisiana Department of Agriculture and
25 Forestry, or his designee.
26 (6) The secretary of the Louisiana Department of Wildlife and Fisheries, or
27 his designee.
28 (7) The president of the Louisiana Farm Bureau Federation, or his designee.
29 (8) The president of the Louisiana Cotton and Grain Association, or his
30 designee.
